  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Genjutsu (Compulsion)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 10</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 5</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 26 | <b>Successes:</b> 6</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 14 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 30</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> C, M</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>This ancient technique was one of the first forms of Chakra manipulation evercreated. You weave nine intricate symbols in the air with the index and middle finger of one hand, imbuing them with Chakra and then directing them towards your target(s). Subjects have an effective Strength and Dexterity score of 3 and suffer a -10 penalty to Perform techniques that require hand or half seals (unless they can perform them without those components). The subjects cannot run or charge, move at half speed, and cannot make more than one attack of opportunity per round.<br><br>This technique can only be dispelled by a character with 10 or more ranks in the Concentration skill.<br><br>If you are unable to see, there is a 20% chance you fail to perform the technique, and you suffer a -4 penalty to Perform when your main hand is not free.</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
